'''''UFC 229: Khabib vs. McGregor''''' was a [[mixed martial arts]] event produced by the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] (UFC) that was held on October 6, 2018. The fight took place between [[Khabib Nurmagomedov]] and [[Conor McGregor]] at the [[T-Mobile Arena]] in [[Paradise, Nevada]], part of the [[Las Vegas–Paradise, NV MSA|Las Vegas Metropolitan Area]], United States.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mmajunkie.com/2018/07/ufc-announces-2018-schedule-september-through-end-of-year|title=UFC announces rest of 2018 schedule from September through end of year|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Staff|date=2018-07-08|access-date=2018-07-09}}</ref>

This event was the most-bought UFC (and MMA) pay-per-view of all time with a buyrate of 2.4 million.<ref name="UFC229BR" />

